      "originalTitle": "",
      "originalComment": "",
      "reviewComments": "On a rather late arrival, past 9pm, my first impression of the hotel is that its not a hotel but a popular cafe. We had to go through the cafe full of people up the backstairs to the first floor. The reception is fortunately very friendly and we were given a front room on the same floor. Room is clean, quite spacious, good kingsize bed. Bathroom is smallish but adequate with good hot water.\n\nWhen we went out for dinner, the location of the hotel is in a 'happening' part of town...lots of cafes and shops around. \n\nReally glad I chose to stay in this hotel",
